The paper focuses on analyzing the well-being of a person through tracking their day-to-day activities, which involves the use of artificial intelligence and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The approach used in the paper is based on fuzzy logic, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with social and environmental factors affecting the well-being of a person, which can be considered as a part of social computing (cs.SI) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for measuring the overall well-being of a person, which can be related to computational engineering (cs.CE).
